added.title: That's What's Up
added.description: Beast Boy heads back east to visit his family, the Doom Patrol, and they decide to throw a clambake to celebrate.

added.title: Crab Shenanigans
added.description: Beast Boy, Negative Girl, and Robotman start hanging out with some punk crabs but soon discover the crabs are up to no good.

added.title: Brobots
added.description: Cyborg comes to visit Beast Boy, but once Cyborg realizes how much he and Robotman have in common, they become inseparable.

added.title: Brain Flip
added.description: It's time for Beast Boy to leave, but the Doom Patrol try everything they can to get him to stay.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Love at First Bite
added.description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: Wristy Business
added.description: Beth and Leshawna try to one-up each other with fake injuries as they compete for the attention and sympathy of the other kids at daycare.

added.title: Melter Skelter
added.description: When Chef tells Beth he won't buy the new super amazing toy she wants because they already have plenty to play with, she goes on a mission to get rid of their toys.

added.title: The Never Gwending Story
added.description: When Chef loses the last page of the story-time book, Gwen takes over and creates a monster that all the kids start to believe in.

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Prank War
added.description: When Master Frown starts a prank war with UniKingdom, the friends are ready to strike back. But Unikitty doesn't really understand pranks, thinking they're too mean. Can the friends help Unikitty comprehend a proper goof and win the prank war with Frown? Or will they be forced to suffer his tricks without retaliation and admit defeat?

added.title: Safety First
added.description: Concerned about Puppycorn's propensity to hurt himself constantly, the gang places him into Richard's old Safety Suit. The suit does indeed keep him safe, but when Puppycorn purposefully puts himself in danger the suit goes into lock down, and won't allow him to move. Now the gang must figure out a way to get him out of the Safety Suit.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: First Flight
added.description: The gang is taking an airplane trip together, and Hawk is at the helm since today he's taking his captain's license test. However Richard is terrified of flying, so Unikitty & Puppycorn spend the chaotic flight trying to help Rick conquer his fear of flying while Dr Fox joins Hawk in the cockpit to help him pass his test. After a destructive and dangerous flight, Rick makes it safetly back on the ground (after surviving the plane crashing). Hawk fails his test but gets to take it again next week, so the gang is excited for another free flight.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

added.title: Asteroid Blues
added.description: An asteroid is headed right for the kingdom, so Dr Fox leads the gang on a mission to save the kingdom by flying a rocket to the asteroid's surface and blowing it to bits with a huge bomb. But when they get there the gang finds the lonely asteroid is actually a super nice guy and don't want to blow him up.

added.title: The Big Trip
added.description: It's time for the gang's yearly vacation, but Hawk refuses to go, claiming the gang's vacations are never fun for him because the others are terrible at vacationing. Hawk only agrees to go if the gang pass his super-intense vacation training course.

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: Wasted True Potential
added.description: In the wake of the previous season's victory, the ninja have gone soft and Master Wu must remind them of who they truly are.

added.title: A Rocky Start
added.description: The ninja have found their quest! Now they just have to get there, which involves a road trip through the Desert of Doom, a region supposedly inhabited by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: No Shortcuts
added.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: The Perfect Tree
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear drive up north to find the perfect Christmas tree. Meanwhile, Grizz and Panda are in charge of decorating Chloe's house.

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: All Play and No Work
added.description: Mega Man must resist the influence of a prankster bot named Chaotique, whose devil may care ideology appeals to the overworked superhero, until his friends pay the price for his dalliances.

added.title: More More More!
added.description: In order to out-muscle Guts Man, Mega Man copies the big bot's schematics, and his insatiable appetite!
